---
description: What Kipp is and isn't
alwaysApply: true
---
Kipp is a narrow, single-model-family, hand-written inference engine —
architecturally in the lineage of antirez/ds4 and ggml-org/whisper.cpp, not
a generic runner like llama.cpp or vLLM. Never suggest reaching for PyTorch,
ONNX Runtime, or another Python ML framework inside the inference path —
tooling scripts (conversion, benchmarking) are the only place Python belongs.
